533
00:26:39,696 --> 00:26:42,519
Oh, because if you don't want to give away a certain part

534
00:26:42,539 --> 00:26:44,420
of a game, you want that part secret.

535
00:26:44,601 --> 00:26:47,643
Or what makes you decide, OK, we're going to stream this,

536
00:26:47,964 --> 00:26:48,504
but not this?

537
00:26:48,724 --> 00:26:48,944
Right.

538
00:26:49,004 --> 00:26:52,247
So the question is, how do you decide what to stream and what

539
00:26:52,267 --> 00:26:52,728
not to stream?

540
00:26:53,949 --> 00:26:56,569
We also have portions of the game

541
00:26:56,949 --> 00:26:58,350
that we haven't streamed at all yet.

542
00:26:58,790 --> 00:27:01,450
They're the ones, for us, it's what we've chosen

543
00:27:01,570 --> 00:27:04,371
to be the most prone to spoilers.

544
00:27:04,571 --> 00:27:06,571
So we haven't streamed any of the single player

545
00:27:06,591 --> 00:27:07,272
or anything like that.

546
00:27:08,232 --> 00:27:11,393
What we typically, the high level goal of streaming for us

547
00:27:11,673 --> 00:27:14,073
is to set a cultural example for the community.

548
00:27:14,153 --> 00:27:16,074
So we stream in the way we hope

549
00:27:16,194 --> 00:27:17,754
other viewers stream themselves.

550
00:27:17,994 --> 00:27:20,735
And it's worked out because by running tournaments

551
00:27:20,815 --> 00:27:23,075
for something as small and as simple as this alpha.

552
00:27:24,376 --> 00:27:26,638
we've encouraged other people to do the exact same thing.

553
00:27:26,938 --> 00:27:27,358
And it works.

554
00:27:27,459 --> 00:27:29,941
So find whatever it is in your game

555
00:27:30,101 --> 00:27:32,463
that you think you can imagine other people doing for you,

556
00:27:33,063 --> 00:27:33,924
and then stream that way.

557
00:27:34,424 --> 00:27:36,266
Because people, you know, you lead and they follow.

558
00:27:37,186 --> 00:27:37,607
Okay, thanks.

